==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: tiānyá héchù wú fāngcăo
===Etymology===
*From "Butterflies Adore Flowers" (蝶恋花), by [[wikipedia:Su Shi|Su Shi]]
*Literally: Where in the world is there a lack of fragrant grass?
===Proverb===
'''[[天涯]][[何处]][[无]][[芳草]]'''
#  No need to be overly attached to one person or location, everything has something about it that is endearing.
# [of lost love] there are plenty more fish in the ocean
===Proper noun===
'''[[天涯]][[何处]][[无]][[芳草]]'''
# [movie title] [[Wikipedia:Splendor in the Grass|Splendor in the Grass]]

===Alternate forms===
[[天涯何處無芳草]] ([[Traditional Chinese]])
